WEBVTT

00:05.606 --> 00:08.674
[rain pattering]

00:08.676 --> 00:11.243
[tense music]

00:16.283 --> 00:17.283
[thunder rumbling]

00:19.000 --> 00:25.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:02.663 --> 01:05.664
[tense electronic music]

03:31.979 --> 03:35.347
[birds chirping]

03:35.349 --> 03:37.416
["Dissolution" by
The Image of All]

03:38.485 --> 03:40.320
But you're not gonna believe
what happens after that.

03:40.321 --> 03:41.670
LUKE: Come on, Max.

03:41.671 --> 03:43.022
No, I swear to God,
it's totally true.

03:43.023 --> 03:44.923
Can I get you folks
something with your coffee?

03:44.925 --> 03:48.393
Our famous pecan pie is
on special at only $1.99.

03:55.536 --> 03:56.735
I think we're good, thanks.

03:56.737 --> 03:59.037
That pecan pie sure
does sound good though.

03:59.039 --> 04:00.939
[Lauren laughing]

04:00.941 --> 04:03.542
So anyway, this guy
thinks it's all over,

04:04.511 --> 04:06.845
but he never
developed the picture.

04:06.847 --> 04:08.247
When he finally does,

04:08.249 --> 04:09.682
the ghost is right in
there right next to her.

04:09.683 --> 04:11.416
It was in the house all along.

04:11.418 --> 04:13.051
That's bullshit.

04:13.052 --> 04:14.685
It's totally true,
my cousin's neighbor

04:14.688 --> 04:16.788
knew the actual guy it
happened to back in Jersey.

04:16.790 --> 04:17.790
Swear to God.

04:19.192 --> 04:20.358
I gotta go to the restroom.

04:21.028 --> 04:21.793
Do you need this?

04:21.795 --> 04:23.095
No, I don't.

04:27.768 --> 04:28.934
Do you have a restroom?

04:31.071 --> 04:32.638
Just down there to the left.

04:34.808 --> 04:37.109
You're scaring Holly with
those stupid ghost stories.

04:37.111 --> 04:38.310
They're not stories, man.

04:38.312 --> 04:39.412
This kind of stuff
happens all the time.

04:39.413 --> 04:40.712
You just don't hear about it.

04:40.714 --> 04:42.781
Ghosts, demons, possessions.

04:42.783 --> 04:44.017
Yeah, then how is it that you're

04:44.018 --> 04:45.317
the only one talking about it?

04:45.319 --> 04:46.551
Are you dumb?

04:46.553 --> 04:49.421
Government keep a lid on
it to keep people in line.

04:49.423 --> 04:50.689
Anyway, your little sister's

04:50.691 --> 04:52.557
got worse things to be
scared of than ghosts.

04:52.559 --> 04:54.661
If I'd have known how
monumentally fucked up she was...

04:54.662 --> 04:56.011
What?

04:56.012 --> 04:57.363
Jesus Christ, she
almost died last night.

04:57.364 --> 04:58.597
We're not equipped for that.

04:58.599 --> 05:00.532
Look, she'll be fine
once we get to I.A.

05:01.335 --> 05:02.701
That's the plan, isn't it?

05:02.703 --> 05:04.303
Get her to California.

05:04.305 --> 05:05.637
Lauren's idea.

05:05.639 --> 05:08.373
My sister and her boyfriend
moved out there last year.

05:08.375 --> 05:10.309
They got all the
treatment you want,

05:10.311 --> 05:11.677
you don't even have to register

05:11.679 --> 05:13.645
or say your name or anything.

05:13.647 --> 05:15.881
They hand out that shit
like candy in Cali.

05:17.084 --> 05:18.418
We'd get there quicker if
we didn't keep stopping

05:18.419 --> 05:19.918
in all these stupid places.

05:19.920 --> 05:22.321
Hey, these places
is what's gonna pay

05:22.323 --> 05:23.422
for our summer, Luke.

05:24.224 --> 05:25.490
Look, a couple more of these

05:25.492 --> 05:27.926
and we'll be fixed
up till September.

05:27.928 --> 05:30.529
Come on, guys, it's gonna
be lit, Cali sunshine

05:30.531 --> 05:32.431
instead of freezing our
balls off back East,

05:32.433 --> 05:33.665
what's not to like?

05:41.141 --> 05:43.342
Okay, so we're good to go?

05:45.913 --> 05:47.179
Same as last time.

05:47.181 --> 05:48.380
Luke, you're on the door,

05:48.382 --> 05:50.849
nobody gets in or
out until we're done.

05:50.851 --> 05:54.519
Lauren, register, Holly,
you just do whatever.

05:55.956 --> 05:56.956
Okay?

06:00.094 --> 06:01.660
[loud rock music]

06:04.498 --> 06:07.065
Everybody be calm,
this is a robbery!

06:07.067 --> 06:09.801
Nobody do anything stupid
and this will all be over

06:09.803 --> 06:11.870
before you can say, make
America great again.

06:11.872 --> 06:13.372
Open the register!

06:13.774 --> 06:14.774
MAX: Do it!

06:20.180 --> 06:20.979
I'm done.

06:20.981 --> 06:22.514
Right, we're outta here.

06:22.516 --> 06:25.083
You people better not even
dream about calling the cops.

06:25.085 --> 06:26.585
We won't.

06:26.587 --> 06:28.854
That ain't the way we do
things round here, honey.

06:29.857 --> 06:30.857
Go, go, go!

06:32.826 --> 06:34.226
[rock music continues]

06:40.300 --> 06:41.400
Jesus, come on!

06:42.469 --> 06:44.136
Holly, you okay?

06:44.138 --> 06:46.204
Just fucking drive, man!

06:46.206 --> 06:47.406
[gun fires]

06:47.408 --> 06:48.473
Was that a gunshot?

06:48.475 --> 06:49.307
Drive!

06:49.309 --> 06:51.877
[engine revs]

06:55.749 --> 06:57.115
What are you lookin' at?

06:59.253 --> 07:01.987
[birds chirping]

07:03.056 --> 07:05.056
Shit, I told you
that was a gunshot.

07:05.058 --> 07:07.159
Look at that, it's gone
right through the radiator.

07:07.161 --> 07:08.860
Okay, look, can you fix it?

07:08.862 --> 07:09.861
Are you kidding?

07:09.863 --> 07:11.463
On the side of the road?

07:11.465 --> 07:13.132
It took my dad years to
find all the parts for this.

07:13.133 --> 07:14.099
It's a classic.

07:14.101 --> 07:15.600
So, what are you gonna do?

07:15.602 --> 07:16.836
'Cause I'm not
about to wait here

07:16.837 --> 07:18.403
and get my ass shot
off by them hicks

07:18.405 --> 07:19.739
coming from the diner
for their money.

07:19.740 --> 07:22.941
Look, if we had water, I
can refill the radiator.

07:23.777 --> 07:24.709
It's just gonna leak out again,

07:24.711 --> 07:25.644
but if we start with it cool,

07:25.646 --> 07:28.380
we can make it a few more miles.

07:28.382 --> 07:30.015
Then we do it
again, let it cool,

07:30.017 --> 07:31.483
fill it up, a few more miles.

07:31.485 --> 07:33.051
We could make the
next town at least.

07:33.053 --> 07:34.653
Yeah, great plan.

07:34.655 --> 07:35.855
Except we don't have any water

07:35.856 --> 07:37.856
and we're in the middle
of fucking nowhere.

07:37.858 --> 07:39.125
Unless you want to
go back to the diner

07:39.126 --> 07:40.525
and ask them to
use their faucet.

07:40.527 --> 07:42.194
I saw a house back there.

07:46.667 --> 07:48.500
Out here, you sure?

07:50.704 --> 07:52.103
I didn't see no house.

07:52.105 --> 07:53.605
It was kind of weird-looking.

07:53.607 --> 07:55.474
I saw it through the trees.

07:55.476 --> 07:57.042
Is she seeing things again?

07:57.044 --> 07:59.110
'Cause I am not about to
go searching the forest

07:59.112 --> 08:01.813
for some non-existent house
your sister dreamed up.

08:01.815 --> 08:03.381
I saw it too.

08:06.620 --> 08:07.853
How far back was it?

08:08.589 --> 08:09.988
Not far, a couple of minutes.

08:14.661 --> 08:17.162
Okay, fine, let's move.

08:17.164 --> 08:19.731
[tense music]

08:24.705 --> 08:27.439
[phone ringing]

08:32.613 --> 08:34.679
Halsey family residence.

08:34.681 --> 08:36.114
Daddy?

08:36.116 --> 08:38.283
You are not gonna believe
what just happened.

08:42.089 --> 08:44.923
[birds chirping]

08:46.226 --> 08:48.727
Oh, sweet Jesus, this is
what you call a house?

08:52.466 --> 08:54.233
You kids must've had it
harder than I thought.

08:54.234 --> 08:55.867
Well, we just need
is a working faucet.

08:55.869 --> 08:57.402
Well, that'd be a miracle,

08:57.404 --> 08:59.604
whole place looks like it's
about to fucking fall down.

09:01.508 --> 09:03.708
Lauren, go knock on the door.

09:03.710 --> 09:04.710
Why me?

09:05.979 --> 09:07.380
Because if there's some
old grandma living there,

09:07.381 --> 09:08.648
she's sure as hell not
gonna open the door

09:08.649 --> 09:10.148
for someone like me.

09:10.150 --> 09:11.751
You really think there's
gonna be anyone in there?

09:11.752 --> 09:13.785
How the fuck should I know?

09:13.787 --> 09:15.787
Just trying to do
things the smart way.

09:15.789 --> 09:18.356
[tense music]

09:19.660 --> 09:22.093
We need something to
carry the water in.

09:22.095 --> 09:24.162
Bottles, cans,
whatever you can find.

09:24.164 --> 09:27.165
I'll let you know
if I see anything.

09:31.538 --> 09:34.239
[eerie music]

09:34.241 --> 09:37.142
[knocking on door]

09:51.058 --> 09:52.058
Hello?

10:02.636 --> 10:03.802
Okay, let's do this.

10:06.473 --> 10:07.473
You okay?

10:23.890 --> 10:28.093
Not bad, not a bad
hideout, what do you say?

10:28.095 --> 10:30.295
I thought we were in a
hurry to get to I.A.?

10:30.297 --> 10:32.998
Well, plans can change.

10:33.000 --> 10:35.300
I don't know, I
kinda like the place.

10:35.302 --> 10:36.702
What about getting
your ass shot off?

10:36.703 --> 10:38.603
No, we can defend the
place, hole it up,

10:38.605 --> 10:40.305
fight 'em off like
in the movies!

10:40.307 --> 10:41.206
[Max mimics gun firing]

10:41.208 --> 10:42.273
[Holly gasping]

10:42.275 --> 10:43.241
Shh, it's okay.

10:43.243 --> 10:44.909
Oh man, here we go again.

10:44.911 --> 10:47.278
Laurs, me and you go to the
kitchen and find some water.

10:47.280 --> 10:48.546
I'm staying with Holly.

10:50.217 --> 10:52.384
Yeah, I figured as much.

11:00.527 --> 11:02.661
[tense music]

11:02.663 --> 11:04.329
I found a faucet!

11:05.098 --> 11:06.231
Open it up.

11:12.005 --> 11:14.406
[Max sighs]

11:17.344 --> 11:20.645
Tea pots, tea cups,
more tea cups.

11:20.647 --> 11:24.082
Damn, you think the people who
own this place are British?

11:29.756 --> 11:31.089
You okay?

11:31.091 --> 11:32.824
My arms hurt.

11:32.826 --> 11:33.692
Okay.

11:33.694 --> 11:34.959
And my legs hurt.

11:35.462 --> 11:36.294
Right.

11:36.296 --> 11:37.529
Everything fucking hurts.

11:37.531 --> 11:38.531
Okay.

11:39.533 --> 11:42.934
It used to feel good,
when I would inject.

11:42.936 --> 11:44.035
Really fucking good.

11:45.572 --> 11:47.706
Made me forget about everything,

11:47.708 --> 11:49.474
all the shit we
were going through.

11:53.180 --> 11:55.280
Now, I have to do it
just to feel normal.

11:57.951 --> 11:59.751
It'll be fine once
we get to I.A.

12:00.821 --> 12:02.120
That's a nice dream.

12:02.122 --> 12:06.324
It's not a dream, we'll make it.

12:09.362 --> 12:10.695
I don't trust Max.

12:11.665 --> 12:12.797
You shouldn't either.

12:15.068 --> 12:16.468
What about Lauren?

12:16.470 --> 12:17.702
She's okay.

12:19.473 --> 12:20.473
She likes you.

12:23.343 --> 12:24.343
What do you mean?

12:25.445 --> 12:28.079
What I say, a girl can tell.

12:32.052 --> 12:33.052
Do you like her?

12:36.256 --> 12:39.924
I don't know, I never
met her before this.

12:41.661 --> 12:43.094
Thought she was into Max.

12:43.096 --> 12:47.799
No, he has a tiny
dick, she told me.

12:49.102 --> 12:50.835
Must be why he's
mad all the time.

12:53.106 --> 12:54.106
Rock and roll!

12:58.645 --> 13:00.745
We make a pretty
good team, don't we?

13:00.747 --> 13:01.747
I guess.

13:04.017 --> 13:07.152
Hey, we could be like the next
Bonnie and Clyde, you know?

13:07.154 --> 13:08.419
Who's that?

13:08.421 --> 13:09.954
You never heard of
Bonnie and Clyde?

13:09.956 --> 13:11.222
You never seen the movie?

13:11.224 --> 13:12.490
Must've missed it.

13:12.492 --> 13:13.992
Hey, look I'm just saying,

13:13.994 --> 13:16.661
like, it would be pretty
cool, like the two of us,

13:16.663 --> 13:19.230
we could just take off,
do whatever we want.

13:19.232 --> 13:20.932
How many gas stations and diners

13:20.934 --> 13:23.101
do you think there are
between here and I.A.?

13:23.103 --> 13:24.403
It doesn't take
more than two of us

13:24.404 --> 13:26.137
to rip one of those places off.

13:26.139 --> 13:28.506
So, what are you saying?

13:28.508 --> 13:30.842
Look, I'm just saying,
sometimes it feels

13:30.844 --> 13:33.011
like we're carrying a
bit of extra weight.

13:33.814 --> 13:34.746
It's Luke's car.

13:34.748 --> 13:37.348
No, no, it's his dad's car.

13:37.350 --> 13:39.884
Whatever, can't make a
road trip without a car.

13:39.886 --> 13:42.520
Shit, look at this.

13:42.522 --> 13:44.223
We could buy two fucking
cars with this money

13:44.224 --> 13:46.791
if we didn't have to
split it four ways.

13:46.793 --> 13:48.326
Four ways?

13:48.328 --> 13:49.828
You're splitting it with Holly?

13:49.830 --> 13:51.863
Luke wouldn't bring
the car if I didn't.

13:51.865 --> 13:53.148
He wouldn't have come at all

13:53.149 --> 13:54.433
if you didn't spin
him that bullshit

13:54.434 --> 13:55.633
about the rehab center.

13:56.369 --> 13:58.570
No, it's not bullshit.

13:58.572 --> 14:00.539
They got my sister's boyfriend
off heroin out there,

14:00.540 --> 14:02.640
and he has been clean
for six months now.

14:02.642 --> 14:04.275
Oh, whatever.

14:04.277 --> 14:07.045
[tense music]

14:07.047 --> 14:08.746
I really need some, Luke.

14:08.748 --> 14:09.748
Sure, okay.

14:13.620 --> 14:15.854
There's not much left
after last night.

14:15.856 --> 14:19.357
That's okay, I'm trying
to cut down anyway.

14:20.160 --> 14:20.992
[Holly groans]

14:20.994 --> 14:22.460
Where are you going?

14:22.462 --> 14:24.462
I'm gonna go find
some place quiet.

14:24.464 --> 14:25.463
I'll go with you.

14:25.465 --> 14:26.998
I don't want you to.

14:27.000 --> 14:29.534
I'm not a kid anymore, Luke.

14:29.536 --> 14:32.003
[scoffs] I know, I just think
someone should go with you

14:32.005 --> 14:33.438
in case something happens.

14:33.440 --> 14:35.040
There's not enough
left in there to O.D. on,

14:35.041 --> 14:36.307
if that's what you mean?

14:38.111 --> 14:39.911
Look, I know you
only look out for me

14:39.913 --> 14:42.447
because you feel guilty,
but you don't have to.

14:44.150 --> 14:46.117
What happened, it
wasn't your fault.

14:46.119 --> 14:49.554
Look, it's safer
if I'm with you.

14:49.556 --> 14:50.723
We don't this place,
what if someone...

14:50.724 --> 14:52.790
I don't want you there,
don't you get it?

14:55.061 --> 14:56.928
I hate doing this
in front of you.

14:57.898 --> 14:59.330
What?

14:59.332 --> 15:00.231
Why?

15:00.233 --> 15:04.335
Because I'm fucking
ashamed of it, that's why.

15:04.337 --> 15:07.005
I'm such a fucking
failure next to you.

15:07.974 --> 15:10.008
What do you mean, next to me?

15:10.010 --> 15:12.410
I haven't been through what you
have, there's no comparison.

15:12.412 --> 15:15.446
You have, and you
were hurt by it too.

15:17.450 --> 15:19.484
You just deal with
it better than I do.

15:21.855 --> 15:22.855
Maybe.

15:25.158 --> 15:28.626
We're just different
people I guess.

15:28.628 --> 15:30.261
I don't wanna lose you.

15:31.097 --> 15:33.564
I don't have anybody else.

15:33.566 --> 15:34.632
You won't.

15:35.435 --> 15:36.435
Not ever.

15:37.704 --> 15:40.905
I'm gonna go find
somewhere quiet to do this.

16:01.461 --> 16:04.295
[dramatic music]

16:08.034 --> 16:09.034
Hey.

16:14.808 --> 16:16.207
You can see me?

16:17.677 --> 16:19.978
Sure, what's up?

16:22.649 --> 16:24.082
You been smoking something?

16:27.721 --> 16:28.721
What?

16:30.290 --> 16:32.323
What are you doing here?

16:32.325 --> 16:34.459
I noticed you had candles.

16:35.528 --> 16:36.528
Can I use one?

16:38.431 --> 16:40.898
You are welcome to
make use of the candle,

16:42.635 --> 16:44.802
but please don't move
it out of position.

16:44.804 --> 16:48.773
I must have a candle burning
at each point of the pentagram.

16:50.543 --> 16:53.177
It protects the
sanctity of the space.

16:58.251 --> 17:00.284
You're really into
this stuff, huh?

17:02.255 --> 17:03.855
You could say that, yes.

17:05.724 --> 17:07.992
You sure you're not high?

17:07.993 --> 17:09.394
You're talking kinda weird.

17:10.195 --> 17:11.396
You mean my accent?

17:11.397 --> 17:14.832
Oh, is that what it is?

17:14.834 --> 17:15.933
I'm English.

17:17.303 --> 17:18.569
Thought you were high.

17:26.613 --> 17:28.079
MAN: What's your name?

17:29.449 --> 17:30.449
Holly.

17:34.354 --> 17:35.386
My name's Oliver.

17:37.590 --> 17:39.891
I'm very pleased
to meet you, Holly.

17:47.300 --> 17:50.101
[Holly screams]

17:50.103 --> 17:51.103
Holly?

17:53.940 --> 17:55.073
[Holly whimpering]

17:55.075 --> 17:56.240
What are you doing?

17:57.243 --> 17:58.709
Don't struggle.

17:58.711 --> 18:00.111
LUKE: Holly?

18:00.113 --> 18:02.814
[tense music]

18:04.317 --> 18:07.051
I'm afraid you're
cursed now, as am I.

18:08.855 --> 18:10.922
The symbol on your
arm is to remind you.

18:10.924 --> 18:13.758
It's the price you pay for
entering into the pentagram.

18:15.762 --> 18:17.562
But soon you'll be
free of your pain.

18:21.701 --> 18:23.534
Asmodeus, lord of despair,

18:23.536 --> 18:25.336
prince of darkness,
hear my prayer.

18:26.973 --> 18:30.908
I offer this gift to you in
the full knowledge of its cost

18:30.910 --> 18:35.246
which I bear with my heart and
my mind from this day forward.

18:39.252 --> 18:40.451
Get away from her!

18:40.453 --> 18:42.920
I'm afraid that's not possible.

18:42.922 --> 18:47.225
Holly and I have to stay
exactly where we are.

18:47.227 --> 18:48.059
What is this?

18:48.061 --> 18:49.794
A simple ritual.

18:49.796 --> 18:54.165
Some spoken words, the spilling
of blood in a pentagram.

18:55.135 --> 18:57.201
You hurt her and you're dead!

18:58.071 --> 18:59.437
That's where you're wrong.

19:00.740 --> 19:03.141
I hurt her and I live.

19:04.577 --> 19:06.144
[footsteps rapidly approaching]

19:07.347 --> 19:10.448
You got ten seconds
to drop the knife

19:10.450 --> 19:11.916
and back away from the girl.

19:14.220 --> 19:16.621
I take it you're the
man in charge here.

19:16.623 --> 19:20.158
In this fucking room, I am, yes.

19:20.160 --> 19:22.126
Well, I like your spirit,

19:22.128 --> 19:23.795
but you're going about
this all the wrong way,

19:23.796 --> 19:25.196
but I'm sure you know that.

19:26.366 --> 19:28.099
A girl like this?

19:28.101 --> 19:30.835
10 a penny on any city street.

19:30.837 --> 19:31.702
What are you talking about?

19:31.704 --> 19:33.471
I'm talking about worth.

19:33.473 --> 19:34.739
I'm talking about value.

19:36.109 --> 19:38.409
To you, she's worth nothing.

19:39.512 --> 19:41.179
A drugged up whore.

19:41.181 --> 19:44.815
But to me, in here,
she's priceless.

19:46.486 --> 19:48.187
And I'm willing to share
the value with you.

19:48.188 --> 19:50.254
Don't listen to him.

19:50.256 --> 19:51.522
He's not making any sense.

19:51.524 --> 19:52.823
It makes perfect sense

19:52.825 --> 19:54.825
to those that are
willing to listen.

19:54.827 --> 19:57.828
To those that know
what they want in life

19:57.830 --> 20:01.699
and aren't afraid to
reach out and take it.

20:03.069 --> 20:04.069
Am I right?

20:05.171 --> 20:06.003
What do you mean by value?

20:06.005 --> 20:07.805
It's quite simple.

20:07.807 --> 20:12.877
A ritual has begun, a ritual
that requires a sacrifice.

20:14.414 --> 20:15.513
And what's in return?

20:15.515 --> 20:19.550
Ah, so you understand
the concept?

20:19.552 --> 20:20.885
Yeah, yeah, I get it.

20:20.887 --> 20:22.687
I heard about this shit.

20:22.689 --> 20:25.556
You sacrifice someone, you
get something in return.

20:25.558 --> 20:26.558
What is it?

20:28.628 --> 20:32.830
Power, the greatest
power you can imagine.

20:34.867 --> 20:35.867
And it's all right here.

20:37.303 --> 20:41.072
The words, the ritual,
the rewards.

20:47.080 --> 20:48.080
Let me see that.

20:50.116 --> 20:51.616
[Luke grunts]

20:51.618 --> 20:54.585
[Holly whimpering]

20:55.688 --> 20:57.555
[Lauren gasps]

20:57.557 --> 20:59.924
[sizzle sounds]
[Luke, Max, and Lauren gasping]

20:59.926 --> 21:01.192
[Lauren whimpers]

21:01.194 --> 21:04.061
What is this, why
do we all have it?

21:05.865 --> 21:08.899
It's the price you pay for
stepping inside the pentagram.

21:10.937 --> 21:13.938
You should have listened to
me when you had a chance.

21:13.940 --> 21:17.842
You're now all cursed, all
of you, just like I am.

21:17.844 --> 21:19.710
Cursed with what?

21:19.712 --> 21:21.112
A ritual was started.

21:22.649 --> 21:25.916
A ritual requiring a sacrifice.

21:36.896 --> 21:40.064
Asmodeus, lord of despair,

21:40.066 --> 21:43.267
prince of darkness,
hear my prayer.

21:46.005 --> 21:50.007
I offer this gift to you in
full knowledge of its cost,

21:50.009 --> 21:53.344
which I will bear
with my heart and mind

21:53.346 --> 21:54.912
from this day forward.

21:54.914 --> 21:55.880
[thunder crashing]

21:55.882 --> 22:00.951
In exchange, I only seek
enlightenment and the strength

22:00.953 --> 22:03.688
to carry out your
work here on Earth.

22:05.925 --> 22:09.827
Give me power, great
one, to use in your name.

22:13.633 --> 22:16.734
Asmodeus, lord of despair,

22:16.736 --> 22:18.836
prince of darkness,
hear my prayer.

22:29.415 --> 22:30.615
NATALIE: [gasps]
What are you doing?

22:30.616 --> 22:31.582
Don't step outside
the pentagram!

22:31.584 --> 22:32.450
[sizzle sound]

22:32.452 --> 22:34.518
- [Natalie cries]
- [Oliver gasps]

22:34.520 --> 22:36.487
What the hell is this?

22:36.489 --> 22:39.123
Dear God, what have you done?

22:41.260 --> 22:44.829
You've cursed the both of us.

22:44.831 --> 22:47.798
Get back in there with me,
it's the only safe place now.

22:49.302 --> 22:50.701
Screw you, Oliver!

22:50.703 --> 22:51.703
Come back!

22:54.874 --> 22:56.941
[rattling and clinking]

23:11.124 --> 23:12.022
[Natalie screams]

23:12.024 --> 23:13.024
[Oliver screams]

23:15.962 --> 23:20.064
Inside the perimeter,
it cannot see you,

23:20.066 --> 23:23.701
it cannot hear you,
but you step outside.

23:23.703 --> 23:26.404
How about we just sacrifice
your punk ass now?

23:26.406 --> 23:28.539
Nice try, good thinking.

23:30.109 --> 23:31.876
I knew you were
a kindred spirit.

23:33.546 --> 23:35.112
But it won't work, I'm afraid.

23:36.215 --> 23:40.451
My soul has long since
been bargained away.

23:40.453 --> 23:41.585
Yo, my man.

23:42.955 --> 23:44.723
You better start talking
some sense real quick.

23:44.724 --> 23:49.059
Go ahead, fire, at
least I'll be at peace.

23:49.061 --> 23:51.896
What happens if you step
outside the pentagram?

23:51.898 --> 23:53.098
Is it worse than getting
your head shot off?

23:53.099 --> 23:55.533
Wait, let me explain.

23:55.535 --> 23:56.934
We're all in this together.

23:58.604 --> 24:00.171
It's watching.

24:00.173 --> 24:01.173
It's listening.

24:02.108 --> 24:04.442
You're telling me
this thing can see us?

24:04.444 --> 24:05.876
Not inside the pentagram.

24:08.448 --> 24:09.480
But if we step out.

24:10.550 --> 24:12.783
So, we're trapped inside
this fucking circle?

24:15.721 --> 24:16.520
Yes.

24:16.522 --> 24:18.355
Bullshit, prove it!

24:20.560 --> 24:23.427
Why don't you prove it?

24:23.429 --> 24:25.629
Take a walk.

24:25.631 --> 24:27.097
See what happens.

24:31.437 --> 24:35.005
No, no, no, no, you take a walk.

24:35.007 --> 24:37.741
[Oliver groans]

24:42.181 --> 24:44.915
[Oliver groans]

24:44.917 --> 24:46.183
[rattling and clinking]

24:47.453 --> 24:49.086
Dear God.

24:49.088 --> 24:50.154
What is it?

24:52.158 --> 24:52.990
What's happening?

24:52.992 --> 24:54.825
He's coming for me.

24:55.294 --> 24:56.294
What is?

24:57.497 --> 25:00.664
I told you, you didn't
believe me, but I told you.

25:05.338 --> 25:06.770
Now, you'll see.

25:06.772 --> 25:08.239
Jesus Christ, what is that?

25:08.241 --> 25:09.406
Now, you'll see what happens

25:09.408 --> 25:12.676
when a soul is promised
and not delivered!

25:18.784 --> 25:21.785
[Oliver screaming]

25:31.697 --> 25:34.532
[birds chirping]

25:36.869 --> 25:38.569
LAUREN: Ever hear of
anything like this?

25:38.571 --> 25:40.170
Not exactly.

25:40.172 --> 25:41.705
[Holly whimpering]

25:41.707 --> 25:45.543
Knew a girl once, her creepy
boyfriend was into it, but.

25:47.013 --> 25:48.412
What happened?

25:49.515 --> 25:50.748
She wound up dead.

25:50.750 --> 25:52.683
He's doing a 20 stretch.

25:52.685 --> 25:53.918
They found pieces of her body

25:53.920 --> 25:55.386
scattered across
the neighborhood.

25:55.388 --> 25:57.755
Jesus, don't any of your
stories have a happy ending?

25:57.757 --> 25:59.857
[Holly whimpering]

25:59.859 --> 26:01.592
Holly, you okay?

26:05.131 --> 26:06.463
I need it, Luke.

26:06.465 --> 26:07.631
Okay.

26:07.633 --> 26:10.901
[tense music]

26:10.903 --> 26:11.903
Shit!

26:12.939 --> 26:16.740
Look at me, you have to
be strong, honey, okay?

26:16.742 --> 26:18.475
I'm gonna figure
a way out of this.

26:18.477 --> 26:20.045
I mean, this is some
seriously dark shit.

26:20.046 --> 26:21.545
If that guy couldn't
figure a way out,

26:21.547 --> 26:23.213
how the hell are we gonna do it?

26:24.850 --> 26:26.617
We could call someone.

26:26.619 --> 26:27.451
Oh, call someone.

26:27.453 --> 26:28.652
If we had to.

26:28.654 --> 26:29.520
What, like 911?

26:29.522 --> 26:30.521
If we had to!

26:30.523 --> 26:31.455
No fucking way.

26:31.457 --> 26:32.590
I just mean if we had to!

26:32.592 --> 26:34.158
Are you dumb?

26:34.159 --> 26:35.727
That is the stupidest
thing I ever heard.

26:35.728 --> 26:37.194
What are you gonna do,

26:37.196 --> 26:38.630
call and ask to speak to
the black magic department?

26:38.631 --> 26:41.665
We're not calling 911 no matter
what happens, you hear me?

26:41.667 --> 26:43.067
All right, forget it!

26:43.069 --> 26:45.135
Can you believe this guy?

26:45.137 --> 26:47.471
I'm stood here with $4,000

26:47.473 --> 26:49.673
in stolen cash and
an unregistered gun,

26:49.675 --> 26:51.342
and this asshat wants
to call the cops!

26:51.344 --> 26:52.576
I said forget it, all right?

26:52.578 --> 26:55.012
Will you guys just
stop fighting, huh?

26:56.916 --> 27:00.217
Maybe there is a way out.

27:01.654 --> 27:03.921
If you guys just stop
yelling at each other.

27:14.233 --> 27:16.800
[tense music]

27:20.673 --> 27:22.506
Well, this is pretty cool.

27:22.508 --> 27:24.643
You know, I was gonna get
some ink when we got to I.A.,

27:24.644 --> 27:27.578
but, what's this thing
called again, an Instagram?

27:28.347 --> 27:29.347
Pentagram.

27:30.983 --> 27:33.017
You know what, I think
I'll keep it as a souvenir.

27:33.019 --> 27:35.886
Remind me how good this
fucking lousy road trip was.

27:39.959 --> 27:41.125
He said it's a sign.

27:43.029 --> 27:44.995
To remind us we're all cursed.

27:48.067 --> 27:51.135
So if it's gone, it
means the curse is gone?

27:52.238 --> 27:54.004
I don't know, I guess.

27:58.277 --> 27:59.310
I wonder how long it takes

27:59.311 --> 28:00.911
for something like this to fade?

28:02.581 --> 28:04.114
I have a lot of scars.

28:06.185 --> 28:07.584
They never really go away.

28:19.765 --> 28:20.898
Cold?

28:20.900 --> 28:23.467
[tense music]

28:24.603 --> 28:25.603
Me too.

28:26.706 --> 28:29.139
[glass clinking]

28:29.141 --> 28:30.340
Hey, do you hear that?

28:32.712 --> 28:34.712
Is it that thing?

28:36.449 --> 28:38.082
It's coming back.

28:40.586 --> 28:42.953
We didn't step out
of the pentagram!

28:42.955 --> 28:46.757
We didn't fucking do
anything, do you hear me?

28:54.100 --> 28:56.700
I must have a candle burning

28:56.702 --> 28:59.837
at each point of the pentagram.

28:59.839 --> 29:03.006
It protects the
sanctity of the space.

29:06.145 --> 29:11.215
Candles, they have to be
burning to make it safe.

29:12.485 --> 29:15.552
There, hey, anybody got a light?

29:17.690 --> 29:20.524
[Lauren panting]
[ghostly whispers]

29:22.128 --> 29:23.594
Lighter's dead!

29:32.138 --> 29:33.138
I'm done!

29:38.577 --> 29:40.111
[rattling and clinking]
[whispers intensify]

29:40.112 --> 29:41.578
It didn't work!

29:43.115 --> 29:44.348
Put it back!

29:45.551 --> 29:48.552
There has to be
one at every point.

29:55.995 --> 29:57.115
[whispers and clinking stop]

30:01.834 --> 30:03.367
[Holly whimpers]

30:03.369 --> 30:04.768
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

30:04.770 --> 30:08.105
It's okay, it's okay,
it's okay, it's okay.

30:08.107 --> 30:12.176
- It's okay.
- [Holly sobbing]

30:14.647 --> 30:16.547
Hey, hey, you know
it's a good thing

30:16.549 --> 30:18.048
you knew what to do just now.

30:20.753 --> 30:21.753
What?

30:22.721 --> 30:24.189
Anything else you
want to share with us?

30:24.190 --> 30:27.891
Any other rules you know about
that maybe we oughta hear?

30:27.893 --> 30:29.526
Leave her alone, Max.

30:29.528 --> 30:30.661
Can't you see she's sick?

30:30.663 --> 30:32.095
Oh, I know what she is.

30:32.097 --> 30:33.097
She's a...

30:34.500 --> 30:35.566
She's a what?

30:44.009 --> 30:46.476
Shh, it's okay, it's okay.

30:46.478 --> 30:48.345
I'm gonna think of something.

31:04.196 --> 31:08.131
Did he say <i> step</i> out
of the pentagram?

31:09.568 --> 31:10.568
What?

31:11.837 --> 31:15.005
We can't <i> step</i> out, but do
you think we can reach out?

31:15.875 --> 31:17.741
Like, if we didn't
touch the ground?

31:18.544 --> 31:20.978
What are you talking about?

31:20.980 --> 31:22.379
Just thinking out loud.

31:22.381 --> 31:24.948
[tense music]

31:29.521 --> 31:32.256
[Luke grunting]

31:41.634 --> 31:42.833
Give me your hand.

31:42.835 --> 31:43.667
What?

31:43.669 --> 31:45.068
Just give me your hand!

31:47.840 --> 31:48.840
[Luke grunts]

31:51.143 --> 31:53.277
Yo, bro, I didn't
sign up for this, man.

31:54.113 --> 31:55.145
I'm sorry.

31:56.015 --> 31:57.047
I'm almost there.

32:00.119 --> 32:01.318
Lauren, grab my arm!

32:04.757 --> 32:06.223
You're pulling my
fucking arm out!

32:06.225 --> 32:07.557
I've almost got it!

32:07.559 --> 32:09.026
[Max shouts]

32:09.028 --> 32:11.295
Oh, fuck it, I can't pull me up!

32:11.297 --> 32:14.665
[Luke gasping]

32:14.667 --> 32:15.766
I almost had it.

32:17.403 --> 32:20.270
Hey, don't you ever pull a
stunt like that again, huh?

32:21.440 --> 32:22.873
You wanna take your
own life, fine,

32:22.875 --> 32:24.375
but don't fucking
pull me out with you!

32:24.376 --> 32:26.076
But I was so close!

32:26.078 --> 32:28.011
She's not worth it.

32:29.882 --> 32:30.714
What?

32:30.716 --> 32:31.648
You heard what I said.

32:31.650 --> 32:34.351
Hmm, take a look at her.

32:34.353 --> 32:36.453
She'll be dead by
the end of the night.

32:36.455 --> 32:38.388
And I'm not gonna
risk my life for that.

32:41.160 --> 32:42.160
Fine.

32:45.130 --> 32:46.130
Don't.

32:47.633 --> 32:49.967
911, emergency.

32:49.969 --> 32:51.935
Don't make me do this.

32:53.405 --> 32:55.005
Yeah, I need a medic.

32:55.007 --> 32:56.307
My sister's going
into withdrawal.

32:56.308 --> 32:57.308
No!

32:58.210 --> 33:00.277
Give me the cell phone.

33:00.279 --> 33:02.813
[tense music]

33:11.357 --> 33:13.056
Sorry, false alarm.

33:17.663 --> 33:18.663
We're fine.

33:23.302 --> 33:25.702
Yeah, just like I thought.

33:48.394 --> 33:51.028
[somber music]

33:56.001 --> 33:57.001
Sorry.

33:59.972 --> 34:01.405
I was so close.

34:04.610 --> 34:09.279
Listen, maybe Max is right.

34:09.281 --> 34:10.347
Well, kinda.

34:13.652 --> 34:18.554
I mean, I get it,
I got a sister too.

34:19.757 --> 34:20.757
I'd want to help her if I could.

34:20.759 --> 34:22.759
You don't understand.

34:24.730 --> 34:28.732
I'd risk my life for her
every day if I had to.

34:31.036 --> 34:33.103
It's the least I can do.

34:35.440 --> 34:36.739
I was so close.

34:49.521 --> 34:51.655
The bag, give me the bag.

34:54.326 --> 34:55.692
What do you want it for?

34:55.694 --> 34:57.594
Jesus Christ, Max, I
don't want the money,

34:57.596 --> 34:58.728
I just need the bag.

34:58.730 --> 35:00.263
Can I have the bag?

35:01.066 --> 35:02.066
Your funeral.

35:12.044 --> 35:14.611
[tense music]

35:49.014 --> 35:50.747
You almost had it.

35:58.123 --> 35:59.389
[Luke sighs]

35:59.391 --> 36:00.390
[Holly whimpers]

36:00.392 --> 36:02.225
It's coming, Holly, it's coming.

36:07.466 --> 36:08.798
[Luke panting]

36:08.800 --> 36:09.800
Yes!

36:34.326 --> 36:36.960
Laurs, look at this.

36:36.962 --> 36:40.463
These two, I'm telling
you, dead weights.

36:43.135 --> 36:46.036
So what, you got
a way out of here?

36:47.739 --> 36:50.874
Maybe, yeah, maybe I have.

37:10.095 --> 37:11.095
Congrats, bro.

37:12.731 --> 37:14.864
Holly lives to die another day.

37:14.866 --> 37:16.533
Just what is your problem, Max?

37:16.535 --> 37:18.702
Look around you, that's
my fucking problem.

37:18.704 --> 37:19.936
We're all in this together.

37:19.938 --> 37:22.105
I mean, why are we
even in this thing?

37:22.107 --> 37:24.341
You know, who went into
the pentagram first?

37:26.678 --> 37:28.878
We spend half our time
searching for drug dealers

37:28.880 --> 37:31.881
who aren't DEA
agents and now this.

37:31.883 --> 37:33.016
It's not her fault.

37:34.419 --> 37:37.020
You're the one who said we
should get to California.

37:37.022 --> 37:39.489
I thought that was
the whole plan.

37:39.491 --> 37:40.590
Well, plans change.

37:42.361 --> 37:43.361
I guess so.

37:44.763 --> 37:46.296
Well, look, I'm just saying,

37:46.298 --> 37:48.999
some of us are looking at the
odds of all of us getting out.

37:49.001 --> 37:52.202
And it ain't looking
so good for some of us.

37:57.342 --> 37:58.342
Max.

38:02.948 --> 38:03.948
Max.

38:06.652 --> 38:08.118
I think we've got a problem.

38:10.889 --> 38:13.923
We're meant to have five
burning candles, right?

38:13.925 --> 38:15.625
One on each point.

38:15.627 --> 38:16.627
So what?

38:17.629 --> 38:20.196
Well, look, look at
these fucking candles.

38:20.198 --> 38:21.731
There's almost nothing left.

38:28.273 --> 38:29.139
Hey, hey, what are you doing?

38:29.141 --> 38:30.707
Jesus, Max, back off!

38:31.710 --> 38:33.276
I'm just using the flashlight.

38:38.617 --> 38:42.052
I knew it, there's more
candles over there.

38:42.921 --> 38:44.220
MAX: Too far.

38:44.222 --> 38:45.555
We can use the bag.

38:45.557 --> 38:47.290
They're too fucking far.

38:59.871 --> 39:00.871
You're a genius!

39:07.946 --> 39:09.979
This is so retarded.

39:09.981 --> 39:11.981
You do it, I don't
wanna screw it up.

39:15.787 --> 39:16.986
Which one am I going for?

39:16.988 --> 39:18.521
Uh, that one.

39:20.459 --> 39:21.459
Retarded.

39:30.736 --> 39:32.902
Nice going, that
was the closest one.

39:36.708 --> 39:38.975
Just needs to be a little
longer, that's all.

39:40.746 --> 39:42.312
Here, hold this.

39:45.650 --> 39:46.650
Hold that.

39:47.686 --> 39:48.885
[suspenseful music]

39:48.887 --> 39:52.389
LAUREN: I think that
one's closest now.

39:58.630 --> 39:59.562
Yes!

39:59.564 --> 40:01.064
No, Lauren, give me the light.

40:01.066 --> 40:02.265
What happened?

40:02.267 --> 40:03.434
The candle, you blew
it out you dick!

40:03.435 --> 40:04.868
[rattling and clinking]

40:04.870 --> 40:06.803
Come on, give me the light!

40:11.109 --> 40:12.475
Give me that!

40:15.347 --> 40:17.380
[ghostly whispers]

40:23.221 --> 40:24.621
[ghostly whispers
and rattling stop]

40:24.623 --> 40:26.923
I think it's gonna work.

40:26.925 --> 40:28.124
Try that one.

40:30.061 --> 40:33.062
Max, you might want to shield
that candle just in case.

40:33.064 --> 40:34.330
No shit, Einstein.

40:39.371 --> 40:40.804
[Luke grunts]

40:40.806 --> 40:42.071
[Luke groans]

40:42.073 --> 40:42.906
Jesus, we're gonna need
five of these things.

40:42.908 --> 40:44.107
It's gonna take forever.

40:44.109 --> 40:46.042
Do you have some
place you need to be?

40:55.787 --> 40:59.923
Yes! [Laughs]

41:01.793 --> 41:03.393
Come on, can we pace this up?

41:10.735 --> 41:12.702
It's not gonna
reach any of them.

41:23.415 --> 41:26.549
I still don't think
it's gonna reach.

41:28.520 --> 41:29.686
I will, if you will.

41:38.063 --> 41:42.065
Do you two have any idea how
fucking ridiculous you look?

41:42.067 --> 41:43.533
We're all about to die

41:43.535 --> 41:46.102
and you're both busy
playing "you show me yours."

41:46.104 --> 41:47.871
What's wrong, Max?

41:47.873 --> 41:49.405
Too shy to help out?

41:49.407 --> 41:50.974
Yeah, I got my own job to do.

41:53.578 --> 41:54.978
Use the flashlight again.

42:02.254 --> 42:03.920
There, there.

42:03.922 --> 42:05.055
I'm gonna go for the
double hit, okay?

42:05.056 --> 42:06.056
Okay.

42:06.691 --> 42:09.759
[suspenseful music]

42:11.129 --> 42:12.495
[Luke and Lauren grunting]

42:12.497 --> 42:14.931
Yes! [Laughs]

42:14.933 --> 42:17.233
Get a move on, that
candle's fucking dying.

42:19.237 --> 42:20.670
Let's bring 'em in.

42:36.621 --> 42:38.354
This one's not gonna last long.

42:39.357 --> 42:41.157
Okay, quick, just one more time.

42:42.227 --> 42:44.327
Do you think it's
gonna be long enough?

42:47.699 --> 42:48.699
I think so.

42:50.101 --> 42:51.601
Hey, yo, yo, yo, yo.

42:51.603 --> 42:53.670
